WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.820
Museum

00:30.000 --> 00:32.000
Excuse me.

00:32.000 --> 00:33.000
My name is Richard Stewart.

00:33.000 --> 00:34.000
I'm a photographer.

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
May I take a picture of you and your little boy?

00:36.000 --> 00:37.000
What's it for?

00:37.000 --> 00:38.000
It's for a book.

00:38.000 --> 00:39.000
You're writing a book?

00:39.000 --> 00:41.000
Oh, it's a book of pictures.

00:41.000 --> 00:43.000
I call it Family Album USA.

00:43.000 --> 00:45.000
Oh, that's a nice idea.

00:45.000 --> 00:47.000
Well, it's fine if you take our picture.

00:47.000 --> 00:48.000
I'm Martha Van.

00:48.000 --> 00:49.000
Thank you.

00:49.000 --> 00:51.000
I appreciate your help.

00:51.000 --> 00:52.000
I'm Richard.

00:52.000 --> 00:53.000
What's your name?

00:53.000 --> 00:54.000
Gerald.

00:54.000 --> 00:55.000
How old are you, Gerald?

00:55.000 --> 00:56.000
Five.

00:56.000 --> 00:57.000
And where do you live?

00:57.000 --> 00:58.000
We live in California.

00:58.000 --> 01:01.000
Well, welcome to New York.

01:01.000 --> 01:04.000
Okay, just a second.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
I'm almost ready here.

01:06.000 --> 01:07.000
Can I help you?

01:07.000 --> 01:10.000
Oh, please.

01:17.000 --> 01:20.000
Hey, hold Gerald's hand, please.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
I'm not going to be here.

01:22.000 --> 01:25.000
Hold Gerald's hand, please.

01:25.000 --> 01:28.000
Great.

01:28.000 --> 01:31.000
Now point to the buildings.

01:32.000 --> 01:35.000
Terrific.

01:35.000 --> 01:39.000
Now give Mommy a kiss, Gerald.

01:39.000 --> 01:42.000
Nice.

01:42.000 --> 01:45.000
Thank you, Gerald.

01:45.000 --> 01:47.000
Dan, thank you, Mrs. Van.

01:47.000 --> 01:48.000
Oh, my pleasure.

01:48.000 --> 01:50.000
We'll be looking for your book.

01:50.000 --> 01:51.000
Thank you.

01:51.000 --> 01:53.000
Bye, Gerald.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.000
Thanks again.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.000
Oh, you're welcome.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
Hey, let me take your picture.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
Wonderful, please.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
Are you from New York?

02:11.000 --> 02:12.000
No, I'm from Greece.

02:12.000 --> 02:15.000
I'm an exchange student.

02:15.000 --> 02:16.000
Well, when did you come here?

02:16.000 --> 02:18.000
Three months ago.

02:18.000 --> 02:20.000
Your English is very good.

02:21.000 --> 02:24.000
Thanks. I studied English in school.

02:28.000 --> 02:29.000
Would you like some coffee?

02:29.000 --> 02:31.000
No, thank you.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.000
Tell me about your book.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.000
Oh, it's not finished yet,

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
but I have some of the pictures.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
Would you like to see them?

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
Yes, I'd like that.

02:40.000 --> 02:42.000
Here they are.

02:44.000 --> 02:47.000
Family album, USA.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
It's an album of pictures of the United States.

02:49.000 --> 02:52.000
The cities, the special places, and the people.

02:52.000 --> 02:55.000
And these are pictures of people working.

02:55.000 --> 03:07.000
Steel workers, bankers, police, street vendors, ambulance truck.

03:07.000 --> 03:10.000
Doctors.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
This is my father. He's a doctor.

03:15.000 --> 03:16.000
This is my mother.

03:16.000 --> 03:17.000
What's her name?

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
Ellen.

03:21.000 --> 03:24.000
My younger brother, Robbie, he goes to high school.

03:25.000 --> 03:29.000
This is my sister, Susan. She works for a toy company.

03:31.000 --> 03:34.000
He was my grandfather. He lives in Florida.

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
And this is my wife, Marilyn.

03:36.000 --> 03:38.000
Oh, she's very pretty.

03:38.000 --> 03:41.000
Thanks. And what about your family?

03:41.000 --> 03:44.000
They are in Thessaloniki.

03:44.000 --> 03:47.000
That's a large city in northern Greece,

03:47.000 --> 03:49.000
but now I'm living in the Bronx.

03:49.000 --> 03:51.000
With a Greek-American family?

03:51.000 --> 03:53.000
No, Hispanic.

03:57.000 --> 04:00.000
Oh, no. It's 5.30.

04:00.000 --> 04:03.000
Um, will you excuse me? I have to meet my wife.

04:03.000 --> 04:05.000
Oh. It was nice meeting you.

04:05.000 --> 04:07.000
Oh, it was a pleasure meeting you, too.

04:07.000 --> 04:10.000
Thanks for your help, and good luck.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
Um, I've got to go.

04:12.000 --> 04:14.000
By the way, I'm Richard. What's your name?

04:14.000 --> 04:16.000
Alexandra.

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
Bye-bye, Alexandra. Thanks.

04:18.000 --> 04:19.000
Bye-bye.

04:21.000 --> 04:24.000
Richard! Richard! You left your bags!

